# CLAUDE.md — Read This First, Every Session

> Auto-loaded by the AI at the start of each session. After a `/clear`, this is how the AI re-learns the project.

## 🔴 START-OF-SESSION INSTRUCTIONS (do this first)
1. Read **`memory.md`** — current state + dated change log. What exists *right now*.
2. Read **`decision.md`** — the important choices already made and *why*. **Do not reverse these without asking the owner.**
3. Skim **`design-system.md`** and **`database-schema.md`** — the source of truth for styling and data. Match them exactly.
4. Then proceed.

## 🟢 AFTER MAKING CHANGES
- Add a new dated entry to **`memory.md`** describing what changed.
- Significant choice (new service, architecture, tradeoff)? Also record it in **`decision.md`**.

